HEADWORD: Palmar
<hw>Pal"mar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>palmaris</ets>, fr. <ets>palma</ets> the palm of the hand: cf. F.
<ets>palmaire</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or corresponding with, the palm of the
hand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the under
side of the wings of birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Palmarium</ent>⟦br⟧
